<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
ROYAL CONTINUES TO DOMINATE FRONTIER LEAGUE IN VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Royal High posted its seventh consecutive boys' volleyball victory Friday, 
defeating Camarillo 15-2, 15-6, 15-2, in a Frontier League match at Royal. 
</P>
<P>
Craig Parker had 13 kills and Ethan Weiss had eight for Royal (9-1 overall, 4-0 
in league play), which is ranked second in the Southern Section 2 -- A 
Division. 
</P>
<P>
In other volleyball matches: 
</P>
<P>
San Gabriel d. Hart, 15-13, 11-15, 15-6, 15-3 -- Jon Flaig had 11 kills, but 
Hart (8-2, 3-1) dropped the Golden League match. 
</P>
<P>
Alemany d. St. John Bosco, 15-9, 15-10, 12-15, 15-11 -- Matt Garland had 17 
kills, Mike Golden added 11 and Mike Finnegan had nine blocks for Alemany (5-7, 
2-2) in a Del Rey League match at Alemany. 
</P>
<P>
SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
Agoura 2, Calabasas 1 -- Agoura's Jill Hartwig scored on Michelle Ray's single 
in the ninth inning of the Frontier League game at Calabasas. Melissa Thatcher 
(11-2) pitched a complete game, striking out 11 for the Chargers. 
</P>
<P>
Maranatha 8, Montclair Prep 6 -- Tamara Silvera doubled twice for Montclair 
Prep (7-8, 2-1) in an Alpha League game. 
</P>
<P>
BOYS' SWIMMING 
</P>
<P>
Agoura 82, Calabasas 80 -- Brad Shenfeld won the 200-yard freestyle in 1:46.64 
and the 500 freestyle in 4:48.68, but Calabasas lost the Frontier League meet 
at home. 
</P>
