EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New York Times Co.: The diversified media and forest products company reported 
first-quarter profit of $35.5 million, down 26% from a year ago. Revenue held 
steady at $423 million. The results included higher local advertising revenues 
at television stations in the Broadcasting/Information Services Group but lower 
advertising volume at its namesake newspaper and a decline in Magazine Group 
earnings due in part to development costs related to Snow Country, which began 
publication in the third quarter of 1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
