<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Time Inc: The New York-based diversified publishing and media firm said its 
first-quarter profit tumbled 26% to $49 million due to a 7% drop in operating 
earnings from its magazines, heavier interest expenses and costs related to its 
pending merger with Warner Communications. Revenue rose 7% to $1.14 billion. 
The revenue increase, due mainly to strong circulation at Sports Illustrated 
and People, were more than offset by higher print order expenses. 
</P>
