<HEADLINE>
<P>
PIG OWNER'S QUICK ACTION SAVES BACON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CALUMET CITY, Ill. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 900-pound pet pig has been found safe in an abandoned drive-in movie theater 
-- four days after the owner reported a kidnaping. 
</P>
<P>
Tiffany Marie's owner, Bob Urbanski, said he received an anonymous phone call 
late Thursday from someone threatening to harm the pig unless it was retrieved 
on the theater grounds. 
</P>
<P>
"He said if we were not there in an hour, Tiffany Marie would be cut up," 
Urbanski said. 
</P>
<P>
The 2-year-old spotted sow, who likes corn chips and strawberry whipped cream 
pie, apparently was taken Sunday from a yard behind Urbanksi's family-run pet 
store in this suburb south of Chicago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA041589-0043 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 44292 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
April 15, 1989, Saturday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Part 1; Page 15; Column 1; National Desk 
</P>
