<P>
SHIP WRECK FOUND IN MASSACHUSETTS BAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The wreck of the Portland, a 280-foot side-wheel steamer that claimed more than 
160 lives when it sank in a ferocious 1898 storm, has been found in 
Massachusetts Bay, a maritime explorer said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
John Fish, co-director of Historical Maritime Group of New England, said his 
crew used sonar equipment this week to confirm that they had found the ship in 
waters north of Cape Cod. 
</P>
</TEXT>
