<HEADLINE>
<P>
BESSIE GRIFFIN; NOTED GOSPEL SINGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bessie Griffin, 67, a contralto whose gospel singing style was likened to that 
of Mahalia Jackson and Bessie Smith. A native of New Orleans, Miss Griffin 
appeared there with the Southern Harps, a group that once included Linda 
Hopkins. She later joined the Caravans in Chicago before founding the Gospel 
Pearls in Los Angeles in the 1950s. The latter group was among the first to 
move outside churches and into nightclubs and musical festivals. They also were 
seen on television on "The Ed Sullivan Show" and "Hootenanny" while recording 
for several labels. Most recently Miss Griffin had appeared as a solo singer in 
Los Angeles churches. In Culver City on Monday of cancer. 
</P>
