the U.S. Supreme Court, with participating in more than 100 Supreme Court 
briefs and with being one of a few attorneys to appear before every U.S. 
Circuit Court of Appeals in the country. After leaving government service he 
practiced with Mitchell, Silberberg &amp; Knupp in Los Angeles, where he became 
known for his litigation, writing and lecturing involving tax law. In Los 
Angeles on Sunday of cancer. 
