<HEADLINE>
<P>
DRIVER SENT TO PRISON FOR CARRYING 6 BOMBS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Northridge trash-truck driver was sentenced to two years and eight months in 
prison Friday for having six pipe bombs in his pickup truck and pointing a gun 
at another motorist. 
</P>
<P>
Frank John Salado, 40, was convicted March 24 by Van Nuys Superior Court Judge 
Raymond Mireles, who sent Salado to prison. 
</P>
<P>
Salado was found with the bombs July 1. Los Angeles police closed a section of 
Topanga Canyon Boulevard near Saticoy Street for about six hours while police 
explosives experts destroyed the bombs. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities said the bombs were powerful enough to cause death or serious 
injury, but they said they did not know what Salado planned to do with them. 
</P>
<P>
Salado had pointed a gun at a car whose driver called police and led them to 
Salado's pickup, where officers found the bombs and two loaded handguns, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
According to a probation officer's report, Salado contends that he found the 
bombs on top of a trash truck he was cleaning while on the job earlier that day 
at a garbage-hauling firm in Simi Valley. He said he did not know the devices 
were bombs, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
