the mile, and Todd Lehman, 16-0 in the pole vault. 
</P>
<P>
In women's competition, USC winners included Leslie Maxie, 24.13 in the 200, 
and Claudia Paris, 166-3 in the discus. Gea Johnson of the Nike Coast Track 
Club led the heptathlon after the first day with 3,374 points. 
</P>
<P>
The meet will conclude today, starting at 10 a.m. 
