<HEADLINE>
<P>
ZEDDIES LEADS ILLINOIS TO NCAA MEN'S GYM TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LINCOLN, Neb. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
David Zeddies scored 9.45 points or more in every event to lead third-ranked 
Illinois to its ninth NCAA men's gymnastics team title Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
The Illini totaled 283.40 points to 282.30 for defending champion Nebraska and 
280.55 for Minnesota. Illinois last won a national gym title in 1958 and had 
been runner-up seven times, including last year to Nebraska. 
</P>
</TEXT>
