<HEADLINE>
<P>
RASMUSSEN LEADS WINGS OVER LAZERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WICHITA, Kan. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Erik Rasmussen scored three goals as the Wichita Wings overpowered the Los 
Angeles Lazers, 6-2, Friday night to secure a berth in the Major Indoor Soccer 
League playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
The Lazers (20-27) were eliminated from playoff contention. 
</P>
<P>
Wichita (23-24) scored the first five goals of the game -- two by Rasmussen, 
two by Dale Ervine and one by Tom Soehn. 
</P>
<P>
Rasmussen scored the last goal in the fourth quarter for a hat trick. 
</P>
<P>
Gary Heale finally put the Kings on the board with a goal 11:24 into the fourth 
quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
