<HEADLINE>
<P>
JAZZ SOCIETY SPECIALIZATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Asking a Dixieland society to play modern jazz is like demanding that a Bach 
society play some Sousa marches. Feather should know that to impose such a 
switch on people who joined a society for a particular style would cause them 
to leave the concert hall or cancel their memberships. You must sell tickets 
and memberships to have a successful jazz society. 
</P>
<P>
HAROLD GRAY 
</P>
<P>
Past President 
</P>
<P>
Potomac River Jazz Club 
</P>
<P>
Washington, D.C. 
</P>
</TEXT>
