<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: WORK TO INTERRUPT TRAFFIC ON FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
All northbound and southbound lanes of the Hollywood Freeway at the four-level 
interchange in downtown Los Angeles will be closed from midnight tonight until 
9 a.m. Sunday for pavement reconstruction, the state Department of 
Transportation announced. 
</P>
<P>
Caltrans warns of "extremely heavy congestion" while workers complete the job 
throughout the early hours Sunday. Motorists will be detoured around the 
project with posted signs. 
</P>
<P>
The repair work is part of a $6-million road project that will cover 12 miles. 
</P>
