<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: GOVERNOR APPOINTS 2 MUNICIPAL JUDGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gov. George Deukmejian has appointed two judges to fill newly created positions 
on municipal courts in Los Angeles and Riverside counties. 
</P>
<P>
Steven Suzukawa, 35, of Los Angeles, was named to the Compton Judicial 
District. He has been a Los Angeles County deputy district attorney since 1980. 
Lawrence Fry, 42, of Rancho Mirage, was selected for the Desert Judicial 
District. Fry has been a Riverside County Municipal Court commissioner since 
1987. 
</P>
<P>
Municipal Court judges earn $77,409 a year. 
</P>
