<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY PREP ALL-STAR GAMES; 
</P>
<P>
KATELLA'S PASTORELLO TOPS SELECTIONS FOR NORTH FOOTBALL TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Running back Joe Pastorello of Katella High School heads the list of 
nominations for the North team that will participate in the 30th Orange County 
all-star football game June 30 at Orange Coast College's LeBard Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
Pastorello rushed for 1,132 yards and 15 touchdowns for Katella, establishing 
career and single-season rushing marks at the school. Quarterbacks Tracy 
Garrett of Valencia, Albert Razo of La Habra, Pete Montera of Kennedy and Jason 
Neben of Orange Lutheran were also nominated. 
</P>
<P>
Servite, tri-champion of the Angelus League, had six players nominated, but 
record-setting running back Derek Brown already has indicated he will not play. 
</P>
<P>
North Coach John Barnes of Los Alamitos will announce his 36-man roster next 
week. The North nominations: 
</P>
<P>
Anaheim: Moices Chavez (OG/DT), Johnny Mountain (RB), Justin Wons (RB). 
</P>
