<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
LONG BEACH RIPS UC IRVINE IN BASEBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Long Beach scored seven runs in the fifth inning to break a 3-3 tie 
and went on to defeat UC Irvine, 16-5, in a Big West Conference baseball game 
Friday at Blair Field in Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Deryk Hudson had a two-run double in the fifth and also a solo home run in the 
eighth for Long Beach (33-8, 5-2). Hudson, who leads Long Beach with six home 
runs, played at Fullerton College last season. 
</P>
<P>
Andy Croghan, a freshman from Servite High School, went the distance to improve 
to 6-0 for Long Beach. Irvine scored three unearned runs in the first inning 
off Croghan. Al Rodriguez had three hits for Irvine (14-22-1, 1-6). Jeff Haak 
took the loss for Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
In California Collegiate Athletic Assn. baseball: 
</P>
<P>
Cal Poly Pomona 5, Chapman 2 -- Wayne Koklys pitched a six-hitter for visiting 
Cal Poly Pomona (16-21, 10-6) at Hart Park in Orange. Chris Cutliff hit his 
fourth home run of the season in the fifth for Chapman (16-21, 8-11). Jeff 
Petredes (2-3) took the loss for Chapman. Miccal Jackson had two hits, 
including a solo home run and three RBIs for Chapman. 
</P>
<P>
In Big West Conference women's tennis: 
</P>
<P>
UC Irivne 6, Fresno State 3 -- UC Irvine (11-13) won five of six singles 
matches to clinch the match in Fresno. Kathy Rose won 6-2, 6-0; Stacey Kadigan 
won 2-6, 7-6, 6-0; Biljana Korac won, 6-3, 6-1; Karin Bering won, 7-5, 6-1; and 
Melissa Vaccaro won, 6-1, 6-2, for Irvine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA041589-0140 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 45253 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
April 15, 1989, Saturday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
