<P>
ORANGE COAST HOLDS ON TO FIRST IN VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dan Murray and Brian Lewis each had 15 kills to lead Orange Coast College to a 
15-9, 15-10, 15-8 victory over L.A. Pierce Friday at Orange Coast in a battle 
for first place in the South Coast Conference. 
</P>
<P>
Orange Coast improved to 26-1 overall and 15-1 in the conference. OCC leads 
second-place L.A. Pierce (13-2 in conference) by 1 1/2 matches with four to 
play. 
</P>
<P>
In other South Coast Conference volleyball: 
</P>
