<HEADLINE>
<P>
CULTURE DOWN ON THE FARM? YEP, YOUTH FESTIVAL AT KNOTT'S 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY, Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yes, that was Snoopy standing next to the piano, but it wasn't Peanuts Gang 
prodigy Schroeder at the keys, just Michael Fennelly, a talented San Clemente 
High School senior who will be performing April 29 at Orange County's first 
Children's Cultural Festival. 
</P>
<P>
Fennelly and violinist Sachiko Tanaka, a Mission Viejo High School sophomore, 
were on hand at Knott's Berry Farm in Buena Park earlier this week for the 
announcement of the festival schedule. 
</P>
<P>
The daylong event at Knott's will benefit the Orange County Philharmonic 
Society, South Coast Repertory Theatre and the Children's Museum at La Habra. 
</P>
<P>
Most of the series of events feature young performers such as Fennelly and 
Tanaka, who gave the representatives of various arts organizations at the 
luncheon a sample of their work, courtesy of the Philharmonic Society. 
</P>
<P>
After posing with Snoopy, Knott's mascot, Tanaka and Fennelly played three 
brief selections. 
</P>
<P>
They included Dvorak's familiar "Humoresque," a piece frequently used as 
background music in cartoons -- usually played just before an unsuspecting 
character is clobbered by a large piece of furniture. 
</P>
<P>
In addition to the young classical musicians, festival visitors will be able to 
sample everything from Chinese dancers and Japanese drummers to Broadway show 
tunes, a Dixieland band and Appalachian Mountains clog dancing. 
</P>
<P>
Other cultural events scattered through the park will include marionettes, a 
mime, a storyteller and an original musical play called "When I Grow Up," about 
the choices and pressures that children face. 
</P>
<P>
Also available will be a Nature Walk Exhibit from the children's museum, 
featuring real stuffed North American animals, and an art workshop. 
</P>
<P>
Discount tickets, priced at $13.95 for adults and $11.95 for children 3 to 11, 
entitle visitors to Knott's other attractions. 
</P>
<P>
The tickets may be purchased from the three arts organizations or at the park 
April 29 for those who ask for the special order forms. 
</P>
<P>
Information: (714) 642-8232. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Pianist Michael Fennelly, Snoopy and violinist Sachiko Tanaka, also 
shown playing upper left, were at Knott's Berry Farm for the announcement of 
the Children's Cultural Festival schedule and a few musical samples. ROBERT 
LACHMAN / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
